 woolly mammoth became extinct as a result of crippling bone disease that left them unable to fend off predators .
It was previously thought that the hairy beast simply died out from post-Ice Age climate change and being hunted to extinction by early man .
But the examination of more than 23,500 mammoth bones found them riddled with osteoporosis and lacking in calcium .
